  1. Patients with oral hypoglycemic agent (OHA) in their discharge summary. The OHA list is provided by John.
oha_list <- read.table("OHA_flat.txt", stringsAsFactors=FALSE)$V1
ds <- dbGetQuery(con, "select * from noteevents where category like '%Discharge summary%'")
ds$text <- gsub("\t", " ", ds$text)
ds$text <- gsub("\r", " ", ds$text)
ds <- ds[, c(3, 4, 11)]

# split notes by admissions, unique: 41103 patients, 52691 admissions
ds <- split(ds, ds$hadm_id)

dischargeSummary <- data.frame(hadm_id=numeric(), diabetesHist=numeric(), 
                               diabetesMedAdmit=numeric(), diabetesMedDischarge=numeric())

for (j in 1:length(ds)) {
  txt <- ds[[j]]
  txt <- txt[which.min(txt$chartdate), ]
  sent <- strsplit(tolower(txt$text), "\n")
  
  # reset for each admission
  hadm_id <- txt$hadm_id
  section <- ""
  newSection <- ""
  admitFound <- 0
  dischargeFound <- 0
  histFound <- 0
  diabetesHist <- 0
  diabetesMedAdmit <- 0
  diabetesMedDischarge <- 0
  
  for (i in 1:length(sent[[1]])) {
    s <- sent[[1]][i]
  
      # locate the section
      if (grepl('med(ical)?\\s+hist(ory)?', s)) {
      newSection <- "hist"
      histFound <- 1
    } else if (grepl('medication|meds', s) & grepl('disch(arge)?', s)) {
      newSection <- "discharge"
      dischargeFound <- 1
    } else if (grepl('admission|admitting|home|nh|nmeds|pre(\\-|\\s)?(hosp|op)|current|previous|outpatient|outpt|outside|^[^a-zA-Z]*med(ication)?(s)?', s) & grepl('medication|meds|med', s)) {
      newSection <- "admit"
      admitFound <- 1
    }
    
    if (section != newSection) section <- newSection
    
    # identify diabetes/medication
    if ("hist" %in% section) {
      if (grepl("diabetes|diabetic", s)) diabetesHist <- 1
    } else if ("admit" %in% section) {
      if (mean(tolower(oha_list) %in% strsplit(s, " ")[[1]]) != 0) diabetesMedAdmit <- 1
      if (grepl('diab.*\\s+med(ication)?(s)?', s)) diabetesMedAdmit <- 1
    } else if ("discharge" %in% section) {
      if (mean(tolower(oha_list) %in% strsplit(s, " ")[[1]]) != 0) diabetesMedDischarge <- 1
      if (grepl('diab.*\\s+med(ication)?(s)?', s)) diabetesMedDischarge <- 1
    } 
  
  }
  
  tmp <- data.frame(hadm_id=hadm_id, diabetesHist=diabetesHist, 
                    diabetesMedAdmit=diabetesMedAdmit, diabetesMedDischarge=diabetesMedDischarge)
  dischargeSummary <- rbind(dischargeSummary, tmp)
}

write.table(dischargeSummary, "cohort_dischargeSummary.txt", sep="\t", quote=FALSE, row.names=FALSE)
dischargeSummary <- read.table("cohort_dischargeSummary.txt", 
                               sep="\t", header=TRUE, stringsAsFactors=FALSE)

cohort3 <- dischargeSummary[dischargeSummary$diabetesHist==1, c("hadm_id")]
cohort4 <- dischargeSummary[dischargeSummary$diabetesMedAdmit==1, c("hadm_id")]

cohort3 <- data.frame(hadm_id=cohort3, subject_id=0, icd9_code=0, type_dm=0, criteria=3)
cohort4 <- data.frame(hadm_id=cohort4, subject_id=0, icd9_code=0, type_dm=0, criteria=4)

Extract the general structural information

The main table includes the ID, age, gender, hospital admission and discharge time, hospital length of stay and survival day. Then we adjusted the abnormal age value to 91.4. Next, we created the binary values regarding 28-day, 90-day and 1-year mortality, and extracted the pre-ICU admission HbA1c value (5430 admissions) if there is any HbA1c record within 21 days before ICU admission. There are total 58976 admissions in the main table.

main <- dbGetQuery(con, "select admissions.hadm_id, admissions.subject_id, 
                   DATE_PART('year', admissions.admittime) - DATE_PART('year', patients.dob) as age, 
                   patients.gender,
                   to_char(admissions.admittime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as admit_time, 
                   to_char(admissions.dischtime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as disch_time, 
                   DATE_PART('day', patients.dod - admissions.admittime) as survival_day,
                   (DATE_PART('day', admissions.dischtime - admissions.admittime) * 24 + DATE_PART('hour', admissions.dischtime - admissions.admittime))/24 as hosp_los 
                   from mimiciii.admissions 
                   inner join mimiciii.patients on admissions.subject_id = patients.subject_id")

# assign age > 200 to 91.4 (Leo: median age of patients age > 90, from MIMIC website)
for (i in 1:nrow(main)) {
  if(main$age[i] > 200) main$age[i] <- 91.4
}

main$mort28 <- ifelse(main$survival_day <= 28, 1, 0)
main$mort28[which(is.na(main$mort28))] <- 0
main$mort90 <- ifelse(main$survival_day <= 90, 1, 0)
main$mort90[which(is.na(main$mort90))] <- 0
main$mort365 <- ifelse(main$survival_day <= 365, 1, 0)
main$mort365[which(is.na(main$mort365))] <- 0

# for each admission, get the first ICU stay ID (use distinct on to the the first row) (57786)
icu_first <- dbGetQuery(con, "select distinct on (hadm_id) hadm_id, icustay_id, 
                        to_char(intime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as icu_intime, 
                        to_char(outtime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as icu_outtime, 
                        los as icu_los
                        from mimiciii.icustays order by hadm_id, icu_intime")

main <- merge(main, icu_first, by.x="hadm_id", by.y="hadm_id", all=T) # 58976
rm(icu_first)

main <- merge(main, cohort, by.x="hadm_id", by.y="hadm_id", all=T)
rm(cohort)

main$dm[which(is.na(main$dm))] <- 0

  if (a1c_prev_icu$hadm_id[i] == a1c_prev_icu$hadm_id[i-1] ) {a1c_prev_icu$delete[i] <- 1}

Glucose

Collecting the blood glucose (artery or vein) examination value, with detailed information and aggregated information (to the main table). There are 785,890 records. We defined the glucose value less than 60 as hypoglycemia and more than 180 as hyperglycemia. We also defined the relative hypoglycemia (RH) event happens if the glucose measurement doesn’t not fall in the range of hypoglycemia, but has the glucose level drop more than 30% from the previous glucose measurement, and the time difference is less than 6 hours. The rapid relative hypoglycemia (RRH) is defined the same as RH, except the time difference is less than 4 hours.

dbGetQuery(con, "SELECT * FROM d_labitems WHERE lower(label) LIKE '%gluc%'") # 50809 abg, 50931 chem

gluc <- dbGetQuery(con, "SELECT hadm_id, 
                  to_char(charttime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as charttime, valuenum 
                  FROM mimiciii.labevents 
                  WHERE hadm_id IS NOT NULL AND (itemid = '50809' OR itemid = '50931')
                  ORDER BY hadm_id, charttime")
#gluc$charttime <- as.POSIXct(gluc$charttime, format="%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")
gluc$charttime <- ymd_hms(as.character(gluc$charttime))
gluc$backwindow <- gluc$charttime - lubridate::hours(6)
gluc$testid <- seq_along(gluc$charttime)

#glu$hypoglycemia <- ifelse(glu$valuenum <= 70.2, 1, 0)
gluc$anyhypo <- ifelse(gluc$valuenum <= 60, 1, 0)
gluc$anyhyper <- ifelse(gluc$valuenum > 180, 1, 0)

# Jesse
gluc2 <- gluc %>% left_join(main, by=c("hadm_id"="hadm_id")) %>%  group_by(hadm_id)
gluc2 <- gluc2 %>% full_join(gluc2, by=c("hadm_id"="hadm_id")) %>% group_by(testid.x) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(rhtests=sum(charttime.y >= backwindow.x & charttime.y <= charttime.x & valuenum.x/valuenum.y <= 0.7, na.rm=T)) %>% 
  rename(testid=testid.x) %>% left_join(gluc) %>% mutate(rh=as.numeric(rhtests > 0))
gluc <- gluc2


ds <- subset(main, select=c("hadm_id","icu_intime","admit_time"))
dg <- merge(gluc, ds, by.x="hadm_id",by.y="hadm_id")
dg$time <- -as.numeric(lubridate::ymd_hms(dg$admit_time[]) - lubridate::ymd_hms(dg$charttime[]))

sum(dg$valuenum < 0, na.rm=T)
## [1] 1
gluc <- subset(dg, valuenum >= 0)

glucby <- dg %>% group_by(hadm_id) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(n=n(), mgluc=median(valuenum), maxgluc=max(valuenum), mingluc=min(valuenum),
            meangluc=mean(valuenum), sdgluc=sd(valuenum), los=max(abs(time)),
            freq=n/abs(los), rh=sum(rh, na.rm=TRUE), proprh=rh/n, 
            anyhypo=sum(valuenum < 60), anyhyper=sum(valuenum > 180))

glucby <- dg %>% group_by(hadm_id) %>% summarise(mintime=min(time)) %>% 
  right_join(dg, by=c("hadm_id"="hadm_id")) %>% group_by(hadm_id) %>% 
  filter(time==mintime) %>% ungroup() %>%
  dplyr::select(hadm_id, mintime, first_charttime=charttime, firstgluc=valuenum) %>%
  # use mean since some adm has two glucose at the first day
  right_join(glucby, by=c("hadm_id"="hadm_id"))

write.table(gluc, "rh_gluc_1118.txt", sep="\t", quote=FALSE, row.names=FALSE)
main <- merge(main, glucby, by.x="hadm_id", by.y="hadm_id", all=T)

Vasopressor

171219 records with vasopressor.

id_vasop <- dbGetQuery(con, "select itemid, label, linksto from d_items where lower(label) like '%vasop%'")
id_vasop_chart <- id_vasop[1:10, 1]
id_vasop_cv <- id_vasop[11:13, 1]
id_vasop_mv <- id_vasop[14, 1]

vasop <- data.frame()

for (i in 1:length(id_vasop_chart)) {
  tmp <- dbGetQuery(con, paste0("select icustay_id, hadm_id, itemid, valuenum as amount, valueuom as amountuom, valuenum as rate, valueuom as rateuom, 
                                to_char(charttime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as starttime, 
                                to_char(charttime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as endtime,
                                itemid as route 
                                from chartevents where itemid = ", id_vasop_chart[i]," "))
  vasop <- rbind(vasop, tmp)
}
vasop$route <- -1
rm(id_vasop_chart)

for (i in 1:length(id_vasop_cv)) {
  # inputevents_cv NO endtime???
  tmp <- dbGetQuery(con, paste0("select icustay_id, hadm_id, itemid, amount, amountuom, rate, rateuom, 
                                to_char(charttime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as starttime, 
                                to_char(charttime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as endtime, 
                                originalroute as route
                                from inputevents_cv where itemid = ", id_vasop_cv[i]," "))
  vasop <- rbind(vasop, tmp)
}
rm(id_vasop_cv)

for (i in 1:length(id_vasop_mv)) {
  tmp <- dbGetQuery(con, paste0("select icustay_id, hadm_id, itemid, amount, amountuom, rate, rateuom, 
                                to_char(starttime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as starttime, 
                                to_char(endtime, 'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS') as endtime, 
                                ordercategoryname as route
                                from inputevents_mv where itemid = ", id_vasop_mv[i]," "))
  vasop <- rbind(vasop, tmp)
}
rm(id_vasop_mv)

write.table(vasop, "rh_vasopressor_1118.txt", sep="\t", quote=FALSE, row.names=FALSE)

# aggregate and merge to main table
vasop_pool <- sqldf("SELECT hadm_id, max(amount) as vasop FROM vasop
                  WHERE hadm_id IS NOT NULL
                  GROUP BY hadm_id ORDER BY hadm_id", drv='SQLite')
vasop_pool$vasop[which(is.na(vasop_pool$vasop))] <- -99 # -99 = unknown

main <- merge(main, vasop_pool, by.x="hadm_id", by.y="hadm_id", all=T)

  • We removed the hospital admissions with age less than 18, and those without ICU admissions, those with less than two glucose measurements, those with at least one episode of hypoglycemia, and did analysis on the data of 44215 admissions.

  • Our study goal is to examine the effect of RH and RRH, so the single measurement can’t reflect the effect and therefore has been removed.

Conclusion 1: RH has effect on short-term mortality in non diabetic patient with high initial glucose level

  • There is a signal difference between diabetics and non-diabetics and also the first blood sugar level.
  • First blood glucose level can reveal the previous glucose condition in non-diabetics.
  • Relationship of RH and ICU short-term mortality varies markedly between diabetics and non-diabetics
  • We didn’t go to intermediate or long-term mortality because that there are more confoundings and the signal may be interfered
  • Although it’s not significant bute there is a trend, using Philips database might increase power by increasing the sample size
  • Figure. Short-term mortality rate
  • Figure 2. Odds ratio of short-term mortality given presence of RH
gluclookup <- c("[  60, 100)"="Initial Glucose 60-100", 
                "[ 100, 150)"="Initial Glucose 100-150", 
                "[ 150, 200)"="Initial Glucose 150-200", 
                "[ 200,2340]"="Initial Glucose > 200")
anyhypolookup <- c("FALSE"="No Hypoglycemia", "TRUE"="Has Hypoglycemia")

glucbypd2 <- main %>% filter(!is.na(glucgt200)) %>% 
  mutate(hasRH=proprh > 0) %>% 
  group_by(hasRH, dm, anyhypo=anyhypo > 0, glucgt200) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(n=n(), medianICULOS=median(icu_los,na.rm=T), 
            mort28Rate=mean(mort28), mort28SE=sqrt(mort28Rate*(1-mort28Rate)/n),
            mort90Rate=mean(mort90), mort90SE=sqrt(mort90Rate*(1-mort90Rate)/n),
            mort365Rate=mean(mort365), mort365SE=sqrt(mort365Rate*(1-mort365Rate)/n))

glucbypd2$dm_plot <- ifelse(glucbypd2$dm==1, "Presence", "Abscence")
glucbypd2$hasRH_plot <- ifelse(glucbypd2$hasRH==TRUE, "Presence", "Abscence")
ggplot(glucbypd2, aes(hasRH_plot, mort28Rate, group=dm_plot)) + 
  geom_point(aes(colour=dm_plot), position=position_dodge(width=.9), stat="identity") + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(x=hasRH_plot, 
                    ymax=mort28Rate + qnorm(0.975) * mort28SE, 
                    ymin=mort28Rate - qnorm(0.975) * mort28SE, 
                    colour=dm_plot), 
                width=.2, position=position_dodge(.9)) + 
  labs(title="", 
       x="Presence of RH", 
       y="28-Day Mortality Rate",
       colour="Diabetes") +
  
  facet_grid(anyhypo ~ glucgt200, labeller = labeller(.default = capitalize, 
                                                      glucgt200 = gluclookup, 
                                                      anyhypo=anyhypolookup))

# 28-day
glucOR <- split(glucbypd2,glucbypd2$hasRH)[[1]] %>%
  inner_join(split(glucbypd2, glucbypd2$hasRH)[[2]], 
             by=c("dm"="dm", "anyhypo"="anyhypo", "glucgt200"="glucgt200")) %>% 
  group_by(dm,anyhypo,glucgt200) %>% 
  dplyr::summarise(c=n.x*mort28Rate.x, d=n.x*(1-mort28Rate.x), a=n.y*mort28Rate.y,
            b=n.y*(1-mort28Rate.y), OR=(a*d)/(c*b), SE=sqrt(1/a+1/b+1/c+1/d), 
            ORL= exp(log(OR) - qnorm(0.975)*SE), ORU= exp(log(OR) + qnorm(0.975)*SE))

glucOR$dm_plot <- ifelse(glucOR$dm==1, "Presence", "Abscence")
ggplot(glucOR, aes(dm_plot, OR, colour=as.factor(dm_plot))) + 
  geom_point() + xlab("Diabetes") + ylab("") + 
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymax=ORU,ymin=ORL), size=0.8, width=0.2) + 
  geom_hline(aes(yintercept=1), linetype=3) + 
  annotate("text", x = 1.5, y = 1.5, label = "Higher Mortality", alpha=0.5, size=3) + 
  annotate("text", x = 1.5, y = 0.75, label = "Lower Mortality", alpha=0.5, size=3) + 
  scale_color_discrete(guide = guide_legend(title="Diabetes",
                                            labels=c("Non-Diabetic","Diabetic"))) +
  labs(title="", 
       x="Diabetes", 
       y="Odds Ratio of Short-term Mortality\n Given Presence of RH") +
  guides(colour=FALSE) +
  facet_grid(anyhypo ~ glucgt200, labeller = labeller(.default = capitalize, 
                                                      glucgt200 = gluclookup, 
                                                      anyhypo=anyhypolookup))

Conclusion 2: RH has dose dependent effect on the mortality of non diabetic patients with high initial glucose level

  • There is dose dependent association between frequent RH and short-term mortality that it might suggest some causality between them.
main <- main[main$dm == 0, ]

Considering more confounders

  • Younger, higher initial glucose level with low SOFA is the highest risk group
glmDS <- main %>% 
  mutate(hasRH=proprh>0, SOFA=cut2(sofa_1,g=4), AGE=cut2(age,c(30, 50, 70)), 
         anyhypo=as.numeric(anyhypo>0), ELIX=cut2(elixhauser_hospital,g=4))
AGELOOKUP <- paste("Age ", levels(glmDS$AGE))
names(AGELOOKUP) <- levels(glmDS$AGE)

DS28 <- glm(mort28 ~ (glucgt200+hasRH+SOFA+AGE+ELIX)^2 + gender + ventilat + vasop,
            data=glmDS, family='binomial')
DS28.final <- stepAIC(DS28, test="Chisq", trace=0)

Z <- expand.grid(hasRH=c(TRUE, FALSE),
                 glucgt200=levels(glmDS$glucgt200),
                 AGE=levels(glmDS$AGE),
                 SOFA=levels(glmDS$SOFA),
                 gender=c("F", "M"),
                 ELIX=levels(glmDS$ELIX)[4], 
                 ventilat=c(1),
                 vasop=c(1))
Z$pred <- predict(DS28.final, Z, se.fit=TRUE)$fit
Z$se <- predict(DS28.final, Z, se.fit=TRUE)$se.fit
Z$bootse <- 1

ZZ <- Z %>% 
  filter(hasRH) %>% 
  left_join(Z %>% filter(!hasRH), by=c("glucgt200", "AGE", "SOFA", "gender", "ELIX")) %>%
  mutate(OR=exp(pred.x - pred.y), 
         LL=exp(pred.x - pred.y - qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(se.x^2+se.y^2) ),
         UL=exp(pred.x - pred.y + qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(se.x^2+se.y^2) ), 
         LL2=exp(pred.x - pred.y - qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(bootse.x^2+bootse.y^2) ),
         UL2=exp(pred.x - pred.y + qnorm(0.975)*sqrt(bootse.x^2+bootse.y^2) ))

pd <- position_dodge(width = 0.7)

ggplot(ZZ, aes(SOFA, OR)) + 
  geom_point(position = pd) + 
  facet_grid(glucgt200~AGE, labeller=labeller(.default = capitalize,
                                              glucgt200 = gluclookup,
                                              AGE=AGELOOKUP)) +
  geom_hline(yintercept=1,alpha=0.3) + 
  annotate(geom="text",x=3,y=2.5,label="Higher Rate of Mortality",size=3,alpha=.5) +
  annotate(geom="text",x=2,y=0.5,label="Lower Rate of Mortality",size=3,alpha=.5) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymax=UL, ymin=LL), width=0.1, position=pd) + 
  scale_y_log10(breaks=c(0.5,1,2,3,5,10)) +
  labs(x="SOFA Score",
       y="Odds Ratio of 28-Day Mortality Given Presence of RH") +
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=45, hjust=1))
